NAME
    mode - calculate the mode of a sample 
 
SYNOPSIS
    #include <acme.h>
    static inherit AcmeStat;
    #include AcmeStatInc
 
    float mode( float *sample );
 
DESCRIPTION
    Returns the mode of a sample.  If there is more than one mode,
    an arbitrary one is picked and returned.
 
EXAMPLE
    mode( ({ 1, 2, 2, 3 }) ) -> 2
 
SEE_ALSO
    mean(A), median(A), sum(A)
 
LAST MODIFIED                               
    980502 Devo
